Pre-Game Insights: India and Australia are set to clash in the fifth match of ODI World Cup 2023 on October 8.
India is one of the frontrunners in the tournament, bolstered by a talented squad.
Australia has a remarkable history of success in World Cup tournaments, having clinched the prestigious title on five occasions.
India has enjoyed a spectacular year in ODI cricket, emerging victorious in four out of five series.
Australia's performance in ODIs this year has been full of ups and downs.
The hosts have enjoyed home advantage in the tournament.
The Chepauk Stadium pitch traditionally favours spin bowlers.
Batting first is generally seen as an advantage here, as chasing becomes an arduous task due to the pitch's deteriorating condition.
